  <datafield tag="520" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Excitonic transitions on the surface of a sphere have been studied in he presence of external static electric and laser fields. The spectrum and the various coupling matrix elements, <math altimg="si1.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mo stretchy="false">〈</mo><msub><mrow><mi>ψ</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>l</mi><mo>,</mo><mi>m</mi></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><mi>c</mi><mi>o</mi><msup><mrow><mi>s</mi></mrow><mrow><mi>n</mi></mrow></msup><mi>ϑ</mi><mo stretchy="false">|</mo><msub><mrow><mi>ψ</mi></mrow><mrow><msup><mrow><mi>l</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>′</mo></mrow></msup><mo>,</mo><msup><mrow><mi>m</mi></mrow><mrow><mo>′</mo></mrow></msup></mrow></msub><mo stretchy="false">〉</mo></math> (for <math altimg="si2.gif" display="inline" overflow="scroll"><mi>n</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>1</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>2</mn><mo>,</mo><mn>3</mn></math> ), between few states of exciton have been evaluated in the absence and presence of excitonic Coulombic interaction with different values of dielectric constant. Variation of various physical quantities: energy eigenvalues, transition probability, orientational and alignment parameter, has been shown to have strong dependence on the laser field and static electric field.</subfield>
